Second Lady Karen Pence, along with a US Presidential Delegation, has arrived in Abu Dhabi to attend the Opening Ceremony and other events of the Special Olympics World Games. The delegation includes Linda McMahon, Administrator of the Small Business Administration, Dr. Jerome Adams, Surgeon General of the United States, and Mariano Rivera, former pitcher for the New York Yankees. Pence and the delegation attended a soccer match between the US and Kenya, where she greeted the athletes and tossed a coin to determine the starting team. They also participated in a Sister Cities gift exchange and enjoyed dinner together. Tomorrow, Pence will lead the delegation and US athletes in the parade of the Opening Ceremony.